-----Original Message-----
Sent: Friday, August 22, 2008 6:06 AM
To: Dancecult
Subject: [Dancecult-l] Global Raver Blogspot - Social Commentary on Global
Dance Music

Dear Dancecult-l:

I'd like to invite you to visit my new project:

* Global Raver Blogspot *  

Social Commentary on Global Dance Music

http://globalraver.blogspot.com/

Beyond visuals and metaphysics, this is a simple, content-centric
experiment. Though personal, it focuses on sharp analysis and critical
commentary. I've already posted a few short entries on:

- Love Parade 2008
- Goa Scene History
- Journalists on the Ibiza club scene
- Laser Blindness in Moscow
- Pseudo "raves"
- Manifesto (my motivations for this project...)
- etc.

The blog also features a new link list. (I'm open to cross-post your URL,
please let me know if you want this exchange).

I hope you enjoy the Global Raver Blogspot! Post your comments, bookmark it,
and come back...

Thanks for forwarding this announcement to those who may be interested.

AD'/TT

http://globalraver.blogspot.com/


"The nomad does not move." (Deleuze & Guattari)

Subject: [sfraves] BSP: This Thursday - The Fingermonsters @ Down Like This!!!

Thursday, August 28th
Down Like This @ Temple (66 Natoma St entrance)
No Cover

Catacombs:

The Fingermonsters (Monsta Music) - Live PA!
Tycho Sean
Swing

Destiny Lounge:

Disco Night!!!
DJs TBA

The Fingermonsters Bio:

The Fingermonsters consist of George Cochrane, Cubik, Andrew Phelan and
Shawn Allen, four friends working together out of San Francisco's famed
Moulton Studios complex. Between their various solo careers and
collaborations, these four have had album and EPs out on labels such as
Amenti, Body Rhythm, Dinner Party, Drop Music, Eight-Tracks, Prismatic, So
Sound and Wide Hive. Together as The Fingermonsters, the four produce a
unique mix of big room tech house, breaks, minimal, and electro. Their live
PA is a site to behold, with all four members freaking out together onstage
on a variety of synths, drum machines, laptops, and general insanity. More
on the Fingermonsters and their label Monsta Music can be found on the site
of their label group, www.prismatictracks.com.

i've got to say this is a pretty dope line up. Faktion usually turns it 
out with each Faktion monthly.. on each and every last friday of the 
month.. and with this month its no exception:


Micron has been a staple of the San Francisco underground for more than 
10 years. Whether hes playing at Revolution or posing as the stable 
pillar of excellence at the infamous Friends and Family parties, Micron 
has always brought something fresh and new to the table. His style of 
techno focuses on a clean, professional, no-nonsense approach with a 
serious determination to make the party go off!

STMLs vast knowledge of music, technical ear and mixing talent are 
immediately noticeable once he steps behind the decks. Taking a 
subtractive approach to mixing, STML prefers to keep it cool while 
taking you to places in techno that are often unfamiliar... yet at the 
same time oh so sick!

RAF1 is a veteran of the SF techno club scene and has been making a name 
for himself as a blogger as of late on gold-code.net. You may say blog.. 
so what? What you may underestimate is the importance of this blog on 
the outlook and history of where technos true roots and influences lay. 
Gold-code.net isnt so much a diggers blog, but is a reference for 
where techno soul came from and where the influences of technos past 
collide with modern days trends.


also.. Broadcasting live from Anu it's another installment of Radio 
Integrated! We've come out of hibernation to bring this party live and 
direct to the world at large.


please find details below:
http://www.defsf.com/radiointegrated/integrated or subscribe to the 
links below at the footer of this message.


Tune in to Radio Integrated, broadcasting live from Faktion from 
10pm-2am Pacific this Friday night at::

http://radio.defsf.com:1200

I know I keep hammering at this, but someone who truly knows said it =
better than I ever will:

"Thanks to your support, Techno is making a HUGE comeback...and of =
course Detroit Techno never left so I'm proud of all the Techno =
producers who did not jump ship to join the minimal craze.=20
Don't get me wrong, I don't hate minimal music. I still love my Rob =
Hood, Jeff Mills, DBX, D-Knox, H&M and early +8 records ;-) ... but I'm =
definitely not feelin' the new use of the word minimal as a genre. =
People act as if the term never existed to define a genre of music =
before. What a shame."

- DJ Bone

X-Spam-Rating: taz3.hyperreal.org 1.6.2 0/1000/N
Subject: Re: [sfraves] From DJ Bone about the "new" minimal.

yeah it's not minimal. i call it new techno or neo minimal myself. if i 
had anything to say about current techno is that it has way more of what 
original techno had before it became minimal the first time around. the 
road where the first minimal went, fizzled out in 99-02ish. you would 
have to thank cologne for it's love of the roots of techno and it's 
minimal edge and divergences amid the late 90s 'swechno' scene for wheat 
techno has become today. i would agree that minimal is a bad term for 
what techno is now. i would prefer to just call it techno and get on 
with it.

while we're at it:
trance is not techno
nor is electro house any close reference to actual electro.

sean.

nico wrote:
> I know I keep hammering at this, but someone who truly knows said it better than I ever will:
>
> "Thanks to your support, Techno is making a HUGE comeback...and of course Detroit Techno never left so I'm proud of all the Techno producers who did not jump ship to join the minimal craze. 
> Don't get me wrong, I don't hate minimal music. I still love my Rob Hood, Jeff Mills, DBX, D-Knox, H&M and early +8 records ;-) ... but I'm definitely not feelin' the new use of the word minimal as a genre. People act as if the term never existed to define a genre of music before. What a shame."
>
> - DJ Bone
>

too much 'cause he like used like tiny font when wrote out the word
"minimal"...

man.. i remember when Forest & Chris did minimal mondays at hush hush back
in the day & it was a fun lil weekly to go to 'cause there was hella
family hangin' out, but I dunno man... the minimal techno, micro house
dealie I heard like the 1st time i went there... it just didn't do
anything for me, 'cause I wanted to dance & I couldn't... it was still fun
to listen to & like seat dance... but yeah...

I mean... Forest had to sit me down & explain to me the kinda music it was
& all this n that.. & I tried hard to dance to it like I would to normal
techno, but it still didn't do anything for me then... & I can still
listen to it now, but I Love my Floor Stompin' Techno Yummy instead...

it's still fun music no doubt! :)

I like emusic.com for their price point, although their selection is uneven.

prereleases, too. I've been happy with a lot of the house and techno I've
found on emusic.

Subject: Re: [sfraves] Online vinyl

i think he was looking for places to buy vinyl, online.

for hard to find vinyl, i sometimes go to ebay.  but you're
paying premium price for sure.  then again, i've never seen my
ebay-purchased records in stores.  you can also buy vinyl from
sellers on discogs.com (also highly inflated).

for mp3s, i HATE emusic.  their search function is awful, as
well as their listening station.  

beatport is by far the best online resource for mp3s that i've
found.  the ability to sort and categorize to such a granular
level makes it easier for me to find the stuff i want.  i only
wish they had longer samples - sometimes i download my
freshly-bought tracks only to find that the rest of the song is
boring or stupid.

m

dance records.com, i would agree, is by far the best.. htfr.co.uk still 
for old stuff. for really good old shit check out GEMM.com. when you 
can't find it anywhere else go to gemm and they will have 4 copies of it 
in mint condition.

 4 walk inz amoeba still has good stuff if you know what you're looking 
for. but don't go in there looking for anything in particular. let it 
find you. be sure to get your fingers dusty, that's the fun of vinyl `;)

i still am saddened by the loss of bpm `;( and we'll miss you open mind.

i think soundworks is still around on valencia? they still rock.

peace love vinyl.. and er 128k mp3 lol `;)

dance records.com, i would agree, is by far the best.. htfr.co.uk still 
for old stuff. for really good old shit check out GEMM.com. when you 
can't find it anywhere else go to gemm and they will have 4 copies of it 
in mint condition.

4 walk inz amoeba still has good stuff if you know what you're looking 
for. but don't go in there looking for anything in particular. let it 
find you. be sure to get your fingers dusty, that's the fun of vinyl `;)

i still am saddened by the loss of bpm `;( and we'll miss you open mind.

i think soundworks is still around on valencia? they still rock.

Subject: [sfraves] bsp:techno listmania

i'm unsure about how people feel in general about "one more list to 
read" but i sometimes feel a lot of people are missing out. i have a 
couple of announce lists you might be interested in reading. usually 
they are mostly about techno related events in the bay as well as mixes 
and sometimes commentary.. which is what def-announce is mostly about. 
the other list is an announce list for our internet radio program, 
'radio integrated' which airs live usually every friday. the radio 
integrated programming features guests from all over the west coast. if 
you subscribe to def announce you would get information on the radio 
programming as well.. so it is advised that if you are solely interested 
in hearing about the internet broadcasts, then the radio integrated list 
is for you. `;)

usually the integrated broadcasts are all good fun with an open house, 
byob and potluck food policy in a loft type atmosphere. we keep the 
volume down to decent level, everyone gets smashed and it's pretty 
social affair with good times generally had by all.

i would invite anyone who shares an interest in techno to at least check 
it out for a month, and if you are not jiving on it, just unsub.

techno news & info: def-announce-subscribe@defsf.com
DEF radio info: radio-integrated-subsctibe@defsf.com

much love and respect to everyone keeping it real out there. `;)

sean ocean DEF
